This paper is primarily focused on face recognition and presentation attack detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with security and vulnerability issues, which could place it under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep pixel-wise supervision could also suggest a connection to the deep learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
